Operation.name: createVerificationRequest
Operation.returnDescription:
Contains created Verification Request objects and associated parameters. Any failures will be returned with the client id mapped to error message in the ServiceData list of partial errors:
    • 188027: The current user does not have write privileges to the Verification Request.
    • 188028: An invalid name has been provided in verificationRequestName input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188029: An invalid type has been provided in verificationRequestType input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188030: An invalid option has been provided in createParameterCopyOptions input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188030: An invalid object has been provided in objectToBeAdded input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188031: An invalid object has been provided in contextForObjectToBeAdded input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188033: An invalid property provided in verificationRequestProps input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188033: An invalid Object provided in reviseVerificationRequestRevision input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188035: An invalid name has been provided in recipe input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188036: An invalid name has been provided in workflowNameToInitiate input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188037: An invalid state has been provided in autoWorkflowState input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188038: An invalid object has been provided in parentVerificationRequest input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188039: An invalid option has been provided in populateFromParent input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188040: An invalid object has been provided in parameter input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188041: An invalid name has been provided in direction input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188042: An invalid object has been provided in verificationRequestDefinition input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188043: An invalid object provided in user input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188044: An invalid value provided in role input argument. Please provide a valid value.
    • 188011: The object cannot be added to the Verification Request, because it has already been added to it.
    • 188014: The Verification Request was not created because invalid type of Verification Definition.
    • 188015: The Verification Request was not created because object has not been released.
    • 188017: The value for the property cannot be changed, because objects have already been added to the Verification Request.
    • 188018: Verification Request cannot be modified in the state.
    • 188019: A Study with name cannot be created, because the Verification Request already has a Study with the same name.
    • 188020: The name of the Study cannot be changed, because the Verification Request already contains a Study with that name.
Operation.useCase:
Use case 1: Create Verification Request with occurrences or WorkspaceObject .
For each occurrence, the system creates the Crt0ValidationLink between Verification Request (primary) and occurrence (secondary). For each WorkspaceObject, the system creates the Crt0ValidationLink between Crt0VldnContractRevision (primary) and WorkspaceObject (secondary).
    • Create Verification Request with valid type Crt0VldnContractRevision or custom type and add content as occurrence or WorkspaceObject.
    • Create empty Verification Request.
    • Revise existing Verification Request object and then add given contents to revised Verification Request object.
    • Add parameters of content to Verification Request object with direction “Input” or “Output”.
    • Execute recipe and add its results to Verification Request object.
    • Set additional properties to Verification Request object.


Use case 2: Create Sub-types of Verification Request with occurrences or WorkspaceObject under parent Verification Request object.
For each occurrence, the system creates the Crt0ValidationLink between Verification Request (primary) and occurrence (secondary). For each WorkspaceObject, the system creates the Crt0ValidationLink between Crt0VldnContractRevision (primary) and WorkspaceObject (secondary).
    • Create sub-types of Verification Request “Simulation Request”, “Test Request” or “Run”. System adds created sub-type object as child to parent Verification Request.
    • Valid sub-types are Crt0StudyRevision, IAV0TestStudyRevision and Crt0RunRevision or custom sub-type.
    • Add content as occurrence or WorkspaceObject.
    • Populate contents of given parent to Verification Request object. Parent Verification Request object is mandatory.
    • Execute recipe and add its results to Verification Request object.
    • Set additional properties to Verification Request object.
    • Add parameters of content to Verification Request object with direction “Input” or “Output”.


Use case 3: Add Parameters to Verification Request.
User may want to add Parameters object to Verification Request.
For each occurrence or WorkspaceObject, system adds required Parameters to Verification Request
    • Set direction “Input” or “Output” to given parameters of content and add to Verification Request object. For other content parameters not in input, system adds such parameters with default direction to Verification Request object.
    • Add all parameters of given content with default direction.
    • Create parameter copies based on given option. If not provided follow parameter preference to create parameter copies or add directly to Verification Request object.


Use case 4: Add Participants and Participant role to Verification Request.
User may want to add Participant and Participant role during creation of Verification Request
    • Add given user as Participant to Verification Request object.
    • Set given role to given user. Valid role is “Systems Designer” or “Simulation Engineer”.
    • If Participant not provided, system sets current user as participant with role as “Systems Designer”.


Use case 5: Initiate Workflow for Verification Request and set automatic Workflow state.
User may want to initiate Workflow and set Workflow state during creation of Verification Request.
    • Initiate given Workflow to created Verification Request object. Workflow can be custom workflow.
    • Set Workflow state to given Workflow. Valid Workflow to set state is “Verification Request State Workflow”.

ParameterInfo.description: Vector of inputs for getting details of the Contract Definition object

Operation.description:
This operation retrieves the details of the input Contract Definitions by reading the attached Contract Package. The operation will return the details only if the package is valid.

For a Contract Package to be valid:
    • It must adhere to the Contract schema. The schema can be found in the dataset "Crt0ContractPkgSchema" which gets deployed to Teamcenter database during installation of the "Validation Contract" feature.
    • Business objects used in the package must exist in Teamcenter.
    • Property names used in the package must exist in Teamcenter.
Operation.name: getContractDefnDetails
Operation.returnDescription:
Detailed information about Contract Definitions is returned. Information contains the Section Group names, display names of each section, object types allowed in each section, common properties for the object types in each section, etc.

The following partial errors may be returned in the ServiceData:
    • 188001:     The Contract Package is invalid. Either the XML has a syntax error or it does not confirm to the Contract schema. The schema can be found in the dataset "Crt0ContractPkgSchema".
    • 188002:    The Contract Package is invalid. The specified Teamcenter business object does not exist.
    • 188003:    The Contract Package is invalid. The specified property for the Teamcenter business object does not exist.
    • 188005: There is no Contract Package associated to the Contract Definition object.

The VCManagement service exposes operations to manage Contract Definitions and Validation Contracts.

The service provides the following use cases to manage Validation Contracts

Get the details of Contract Definition object
ServiceInterface.name: VCManagement

StructElement.description: The object (BOMLine or WorkspaceObject) that is to be added.
StructElement.name: objectToBeAdded

StructElement.description: PS Occurrence Thread child path. If objectToBeAdded is empty, object determined from childPathObjectToBeAdded will be added to Verification Request. System considers either objectToBeAdded or childPathObjectToBeAdded to add to Verification Request. childPathObjectToBeAdded works on existing BOM window in system. The BOM window must be available in system to determine and add object to Verification Request.
StructElement.name: childPathObjectToBeAdded

StructElement.description: The context (BOMLine) in which Tracelink is to be created. This is required when objectToBeAdded is of type BOMLine, and ignored when objectToBeAdded is of type WorkspaceObject.
StructElement.name: contextForObjectToBeAdded

StructElement.description: PS Occurrence Thread child path. If contextForObjectToBeAdded is empty, context of objectToBeAdded will be determined from childPathContextToBeAdded. System considers either contextForObjectToBeAdded or childPathContextToBeAdded as context. childPathContextToBeAdded works on existing BOM window in system. The BOM window must be available in system to determine and add object to Verification Request.
StructElement.name: childPathContextToBeAdded

StructElement.description: Additional properties for objectToBeAdded.
StructElement.name: additionalProps

StructElement.description: The direction to be set for parameter. Valid values are: “Input”, “Output” or empty. “Input” or empty direction parameters will be set as input to Verification Request. “Output” direction parameters will be set as output of Verification Request.
StructElement.name: direction

StructElement.description: The User object to be added as Participant to Verification Request.

StructElement.name: bomWindows

Struct.description: Structure represents Information about recipe to be executed on the given content.

StructElement.description: A list of ContractDefnOutput objects detailing information of the Contract Definition.
StructElement.name: contractDefnOutputs

StructElement.description: This is an SOA Service Data structure.
StructElement.name: serviceData

Struct.description: This structure contains detailed information about Contract Definitions. The information contains  Section Group names, Section display names, allowed object types for each Section, and common properties for the object types in each Section, etc.
Struct.name: ContractDefnResponse

StructElement.description: Display name of Contract Definition Section
StructElement.name: displayName

StructElement.description: A list of object types and quantities that must be displayed in a section.
StructElement.name: objectInfos

StructElement.description: Teamcenter object properties that must be displayed in a section. These properties are common to all the objects in the section.
StructElement.name: propertyNames

StructElement.description: Teamcenter object property's display name.
StructElement.name: propertyDisplayNames

Struct.description: This structure contains detailed information of the sections specified within a group in a Contract Definition.
Struct.name: ContractDefnSection

StructElement.description: This unique Id is used to identify return data elements and partial errors associated with this input structure.
StructElement.name: clientID

StructElement.description: Created Verification Request Object.
StructElement.name: verificationRequest

StructElement.description: A List of ElementData structure. Represents details of elements of Verification Request Object.
StructElement.name: elements

Struct.description: Structure represents created Verification Request object and related data.
Struct.name: CreateVerificationRequestData

StructElement.description: This unique ID is used to identify return data elements and partial errors associated with this input structure.
StructElement.name: clientID

StructElement.description: Verification Request object name. It is mandatory input to create Crt0VldnContractRevision object.
StructElement.name: verificationRequestName

StructElement.description: Workflow to initiate for Verification Request object. Workflow can be custom Workflow or default system workflow “Verification Request State Workflow”.   Default system workflow “Verification Request State Workflow” manages Verification Request with states “Authoring”, "Submitted", "Analyzed", "Publishing" and "Complete". If empty, no workflow will be set to Verification Request.
StructElement.name: workflowNameToInitiate

StructElement.description: If true, created Verification Request is populated from given parentVerificationRequest parent content. If false, content of parentVerificationRequest parent will not be populated to created Verification Request.
StructElement.name: populateFromParent

StructElement.description: Parent Verification Request Object for creating sub-type of Verification Request object. It is mandatory only for creation of sub-types of Verification Request object.
StructElement.name: parentVRObject

StructElement.description: Verification Request object type. Valid types are Crt0VldnContractRevision and its sub-types
StructElement.name: verificationRequestType

StructElement.description: Optional Crt0VCDefnRevision object. If not empty , system sets given Verification Definition Revision to created Verification Request object. If empty, Verification Definition Revision information will be empty for created Verification Request object.
StructElement.name: verificationRequestDefinition

StructElement.description: Existing Crt0VldnContractRevision Verification Request Object. If not empty, system performs Revise operation on existing Verification Request and adds given input objects to revised Verification Request object. If empty, system creates new Verification Request object and adds given input objects.
StructElement.name: reviseVerificationRequestRevision

StructElement.description: A list of AddObjectInput structure. Represents content and parameters details to add to Verification Request Object.
StructElement.name: verificationRequestContent

StructElement.description:
This option to set given parameter directly or create copy and then set to Verification Request object.
The parameter copy options are: “Input”, “Output” or “Input,Output” and “” (empty).
“Input” - copies of input parameters are created.
“Output” - copies of output parameters are created.
“Input,Output” - copies of input and output parameters are created.
“” (empty) – system preference "PLE_AnalysisRequest_CopyAttribute" is used to determine what parameters are copied.
StructElement.name: createParameterCopyOptions

StructElement.description: Additional properties to set on Verification Request object.
StructElement.name: verificationRequestProps

StructElement.description: The recipe to be executed on given verificationRequestContent content . The results are added to the Verification Request.
StructElement.name: recipeData

StructElement.description: A list of ParticipantInfo structure. Represents details about participants to be added to Verification Request object. If empty, current user will be set as Participant with role as “Systems Designer”.
StructElement.name: participants

StructElement.name: type

StructElement.description:
Number of objects of a given type. Allowed values are:
a.    "0" (Zero)

b.    Any positive number
Example: Value of 1 allows only one object of the given type in the section.

c.    "*". Value of * allows any number of objects of the given type in the section.

Direction of parameter object. Supported values are “Input” and “Output”.
"Input" parameter represents input to Verification Request.
"Output" parameter represents output of Verification Request.
